---
title: Tourongo — Waitlist & Seat Promotion Logic
---

sequenceDiagram
    participant T1 as Traveler 1\n(waitlist pos 1)
    participant T2 as Traveler 2\n(waitlist pos 2)
    participant T3 as Existing Booking\n(cancels)
    participant API as BookingService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant WS as WebSocket

    Note over T1,WS: Scenario: Tour is FULL. T1 and T2 join waitlist.

    T1->>API: POST /api/traveler/waitlist {occurrenceId, peopleCount=2}
    API->>DB: INSERT waitlist_entry (position=1, status=WAITING, peopleCount=2)
    API-->>T1: You are #1 in queue

    T2->>API: POST /api/traveler/waitlist {occurrenceId, peopleCount=5}
    API->>DB: INSERT waitlist_entry (position=2, status=WAITING, peopleCount=5)
    API-->>T2: You are #2 in queue

    Note over T3,WS: Existing confirmed traveler cancels their 3-seat booking

    T3->>API: DELETE /api/traveler/bookings/{id}
    API->>DB: SELECT ... FOR UPDATE (lock occurrence)
    API->>DB: UPDATE booking SET status=Cancelled
    API->>DB: seatsReserved -= 3  (now 3 free seats)
    API->>DB: Process refund based on cancellation timing

    Note over API,WS: Waitlist promotion logic

    API->>DB: SELECT waitlist WHERE occurrenceId=? AND status=WAITING ORDER BY position ASC
    Note over API: T1 needs 2 seats. 3 available. 2 ≤ 3 ✅
    API->>DB: seatsReserved += 2 (T1's count)
    API->>DB: UPDATE T1 waitlist_entry SET status=PROMOTED, promotedAt=now
    API->>DB: INSERT booking for T1 (status=PendingPayment, cartExpiresAt=now+15min)
    API->>WS: Notify T1: "You've been promoted! 15min to pay"
    Note over API: T2 needs 5 seats. 1 remaining. 5 > 1 ❌ SKIP
    Note over API: T2 stays in queue at position 2
    Note over API: (If T3 had freed 5+ seats, T2 would be promoted instead)

    Note over T1,WS: T1 must pay within 15 minutes

    alt T1 pays in time
        T1->>API: POST /api/payments/create-session
        Note over API: Stripe checkout flow (see payment diagram)
        API->>DB: UPDATE booking SET status=Confirmed
    else T1 does not pay (PaymentTimeoutJob)
        Note over API: PaymentTimeoutJob fires
        API->>DB: UPDATE T1 booking SET status=Expired
        API->>DB: seatsReserved -= 2 (seats freed again)
        Note over API: Repeat promotion check — T2 still needs 5, only 2 free → still skipped
    end
